# {{.Name}} ({{.Type}})

Manages a Cross-Cluster Replication (CCR) auto-follow pattern. See the [Cross-Cluster Replication documentation](https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/ccr-auto-follow.html) for more details.

**NOTE:** CCR requires a Platinum or Enterprise license (trial mode enables these features on development clusters).

This resource uses `active` (boolean) for pause/resume, mirroring the auto-follow API. The follower index resource uses `status` (`"active"` / `"paused"`) because the CCR follow info API returns a string status enum.

Configure remote cluster connectivity separately, for example with [`elasticstack_elasticsearch_cluster_settings`](elasticsearch_cluster_settings).

